sentences.english: Replaceability is limited to changing the dependency to depend on something different.
sentences.chinese: 可替换性仅限于修改依赖关系以依赖不同的内容。

sentences.english: To replace a standard tracheostomy tube.
sentences.chinese: 替换一般标准型气切管。

sentences.english: Replaces the item at the specified index with a new object.
sentences.chinese: 使用指定项替换指定索引处的项。

sentences.english: This is good, since you want to substitute values from files instead.
sentences.chinese: 这样很好，因为您想要用来自文件的替换值来代替。

sentences.english: Replacing thiomersal in vaccines would require regulatory approval.
sentences.chinese: 替换疫苗中的硫柳汞还需要管制审批。

sentences.english: When measuring the lower torque, replace to with a liny spring.
sentences.chinese: 当测量小扭力时，用细弹簧替换粗弹簧。

sentences.english: With these components, you are ready to begin the process of automatic dialogue replacement, " or "ADR" for short.
sentences.chinese: 借助于这些资料，你便可以开始自动对白替换工作。

sentences.english: Substitution characters are not introduced during parsing or serialization on the server.
sentences.chinese: 在服务器上，解析或串行化不会引入替换字符。

sentences.english: Old meade afraid daughter hard tom green leaves, m blue home, two people to replace.
sentences.chinese: 老米怕女儿辛苦让米青留下，米蓝回家，两人替换。

sentences.english: A suitcase is enough to take your clothes with you on holiday.
sentences.chinese: 一只手提箱足够装得下度假时替换的衣服。

sentences.english: The improved embryonic array realizes tolerance with cell-elimination.
sentences.chinese: 改进后的胚胎阵列采用单细胞替换法实现容错。

sentences.english: After the earlier invasion, Celtic had been replaced with English.
sentences.chinese: 早期的侵略后，凯尔特语被替换成英语。

sentences.english: The tokens are replaced with the fully qualified value.
sentences.chinese: 将标记替换为完全限定值。

sentences.english: Replace sequences of white-space within the string with a single space.
sentences.chinese: 在字符串内使用单空格替换连续的空白。
